==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fantail
<hw>Fan"tail`</hw> <pr>(f⟦acr⟧n"t⟦amac⟧l`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A variety of the domestic pigeon,
so called from the shape of the tail.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Any bird
of the Australian genus <gen>Rhipidura</gen>, in which the tail is
spread in the form of a fan during flight. They belong to the family of
flycatchers.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>the <er>fantail
goldfish</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fan-tailed</ent>⟦br⟧
